WEBVTT

00:01:15.700 --> 00:01:20.940
=About Love=

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:23.940
=Episode 1=

00:01:25.980 --> 00:01:27.620
Have you ever felt like

00:01:27.740 --> 00:01:30.260
you're a character in a play?

00:01:31.380 --> 00:01:32.980
Every action you take,

00:01:33.100 --> 00:01:34.410
every word you say,

00:01:37.410 --> 00:01:39.020
feels like part of a written script.

00:01:40.770 --> 00:01:42.380
When you talk like that,

00:01:43.820 --> 00:01:44.980
it's incredibly charming.

00:01:46.050 --> 00:01:48.620
Lucy, I love you.

00:01:49.050 --> 00:01:50.260
What exactly do you love about me?

00:01:50.460 --> 00:01:53.540
The universe made someone
as perfect as you

00:01:53.540 --> 00:01:54.690
to draw me in.

00:01:55.180 --> 00:01:56.210
Every time

00:01:56.210 --> 00:01:57.290
I see you,

00:01:57.850 --> 00:01:59.690
all my worries

00:01:59.900 --> 00:02:01.130
simply disappear.

00:02:01.740 --> 00:02:02.980
Only happiness remains.

00:02:04.850 --> 00:02:05.740
Aren't you afraid

00:02:05.740 --> 00:02:07.820
your girlfriend might
find out about your talk?

00:02:10.780 --> 00:02:11.620
Honey...

00:02:12.170 --> 00:02:13.010
Let me explain!

00:02:13.260 --> 00:02:15.410
Fine, I'm listening...

00:02:17.220 --> 00:02:18.060
Stop pulling!

00:02:19.730 --> 00:02:21.290
Please, just hear me out!

00:02:21.540 --> 00:02:22.500
I'll beat you up!

00:02:25.570 --> 00:02:26.980
(Our teacher once said in school)

00:02:27.660 --> 00:02:30.100
(that a person must know
what they truly want.)

00:02:30.570 --> 00:02:32.340
(Only then can they work hard for it.)

00:02:32.820 --> 00:02:34.260
(But sometimes,)

00:02:34.260 --> 00:02:36.010
(life will inform you without warning)

00:02:36.500 --> 00:02:38.540
(that what you want
doesn't really matter.)

00:02:39.060 --> 00:02:41.170
(Because when we come into this world,)

00:02:41.290 --> 00:02:45.010
(we may have already been
given our own purpose.)

00:02:45.010 --> 00:02:45.850
Li Xiaoxi!

00:02:53.850 --> 00:02:54.690
Here's your water.

00:02:54.690 --> 00:02:56.220
Thanks, Xiaoxi.

00:02:56.780 --> 00:02:58.610
By the way, this is my boyfriend,

00:02:58.780 --> 00:02:59.980
Zhou Xiaolong, from Class 3.

00:03:00.730 --> 00:03:01.660
Hello.

00:03:05.540 --> 00:03:06.410
I like you.

00:03:06.780 --> 00:03:08.170
Hey, the first time I saw you, I...

00:03:08.290 --> 00:03:09.540
I fell for you right away.

00:03:11.130 --> 00:03:11.970
Excuse me,

00:03:12.290 --> 00:03:13.730
isn't Ting with you?

00:03:14.570 --> 00:03:15.690
Your girlfriend
has class this afternoon.

00:03:16.730 --> 00:03:17.890
Are you free today?

00:03:18.500 --> 00:03:19.820
I have two movie tickets
for this afternoon.

00:03:20.010 --> 00:03:20.850
(I used to think)

00:03:20.980 --> 00:03:22.820
(such things would happen occasionally,)

00:03:23.340 --> 00:03:24.730
(and such people should be a minority.)

00:03:26.610 --> 00:03:27.540
(Unfortunately, sometimes,)

00:03:27.540 --> 00:03:29.100
(growing up just proves)

00:03:29.100 --> 00:03:30.100
(how naive I was.)

00:03:30.100 --> 00:03:32.290
Xiaoxi, I've got some news for you.

00:03:33.690 --> 00:03:35.690
Bai and I

00:03:36.010 --> 00:03:36.890
are getting married.

00:03:37.170 --> 00:03:39.610
Let me tell you, I think
we're perfect for each other.

00:03:39.940 --> 00:03:41.890
We love the same kind of food.

00:03:42.130 --> 00:03:43.940
We travel to all the same places.

00:03:44.410 --> 00:03:45.690
What's that saying?

00:03:46.060 --> 00:03:47.380
Meant to be.

00:03:48.180 --> 00:03:49.040
Ah,

00:03:49.060 --> 00:03:50.780
yeah. Right now,

00:03:50.780 --> 00:03:52.170
there's only Yingtao in my heart.

00:03:53.220 --> 00:03:54.380
Oh, sorry.

00:03:54.570 --> 00:03:55.410
Did I step on you?

00:03:55.410 --> 00:03:56.690
Ah, it's fine.

00:03:57.100 --> 00:03:58.890
(As this kind of thing
happens more often,)

00:03:59.100 --> 00:04:00.450
(I've slowly gotten used to it.)

00:04:01.220 --> 00:04:02.260
(All those messy people and things)

00:04:02.260 --> 00:04:03.720
- (keep coming.)
- Here, have a cherry.

00:04:03.730 --> 00:04:05.690
(It's like when the heavens made me,)

00:04:06.010 --> 00:04:08.100
(they only wrote one story for me.)

00:04:08.610 --> 00:04:09.980
(Love)

00:04:09.980 --> 00:04:10.940
(is dazzlingly brilliant)

00:04:10.940 --> 00:04:12.100
(and hard to tell what's real.)

00:04:12.410 --> 00:04:13.940
(You think it's true love arriving,)

00:04:14.260 --> 00:04:16.660
(only to find lies behind sweet words.)

00:04:17.610 --> 00:04:20.250
(So, I won't remain silent any longer.)

00:04:20.930 --> 00:04:21.790
Here.

00:04:22.060 --> 00:04:24.340
(I have to do something for them.)

00:04:25.900 --> 00:04:27.580
Can I ask you

00:04:27.580 --> 00:04:28.660
a rather personal question?

00:04:29.340 --> 00:04:30.700
Do you

00:04:30.700 --> 00:04:31.850
make a living from this?

00:04:32.280 --> 00:04:33.120
Don't worry.

00:04:33.130 --> 00:04:35.490
Since I'm here willingly,
I won't take a penny.

00:04:36.050 --> 00:04:37.490
After all, the youth of women

00:04:37.490 --> 00:04:39.170
who gave everything
only to be failed by men

00:04:39.170 --> 00:04:40.850
is priceless.

00:04:40.850 --> 00:04:41.700
Right?

00:04:41.710 --> 00:04:42.730
May I ask why?

00:04:42.980 --> 00:04:44.730
Because we're both women.

00:04:44.850 --> 00:04:45.980
Actually, my boyfriend and I

00:04:45.980 --> 00:04:47.460
have been together for six years.

00:04:47.460 --> 00:04:49.140
Our relationship has always been solid.

00:04:49.290 --> 00:04:51.700
He even proposed to me last week.

00:04:51.700 --> 00:04:52.540
And I said yes.

00:04:52.780 --> 00:04:53.660
So,

00:04:53.930 --> 00:04:54.980
I don't think

00:04:55.290 --> 00:04:56.290
your appearance alone

00:04:56.460 --> 00:04:57.580
is enough to make him turn on me.

00:04:57.700 --> 00:04:58.900
I believe you asked to meet me

00:04:58.900 --> 00:05:00.460
to verify this very point.

00:05:00.780 --> 00:05:02.370
Would you investigate and follow him?

00:05:02.780 --> 00:05:04.100
I don't need to do anything.

00:05:05.140 --> 00:05:07.490
All I have to do is show up
in front of your boyfriend.

00:05:08.730 --> 00:05:09.700
Wait a moment!

00:05:21.250 --> 00:05:22.250
Forgive my bluntness,

00:05:23.290 --> 00:05:24.490
do you really think

00:05:24.780 --> 00:05:25.980
that appearing in front of my boyfriend

00:05:26.140 --> 00:05:28.050
with your looks

00:05:28.290 --> 00:05:30.020
would make him obsessed with you?

00:05:30.290 --> 00:05:32.020
Sometimes, men don't need

00:05:32.020 --> 00:05:33.460
a woman to be stunning.

00:05:34.140 --> 00:05:35.410
They just lack

00:05:35.660 --> 00:05:37.250
a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.

00:05:37.780 --> 00:05:38.730
What a coincidence.

00:05:43.020 --> 00:05:44.460
Yeah, what a coincidence.

00:05:44.980 --> 00:05:46.100
I was just thinking about

00:05:46.100 --> 00:05:47.460
how I ran into you again.

00:05:47.810 --> 00:05:48.780
I haven't seen you before.

00:05:49.220 --> 00:05:50.140
New here?

00:05:51.070 --> 00:05:51.910
Yeah.

00:05:51.930 --> 00:05:54.140
I'm interning at the design company
on the 15th floor.

00:05:54.660 --> 00:05:55.580
9th floor.

00:05:55.930 --> 00:05:57.340
The travel agency planning director.

00:05:58.930 --> 00:06:00.250
You may call me

00:06:02.050 --> 00:06:02.890
Mr. Zhang.

00:06:03.050 --> 00:06:05.540
You do private customized tours, right?

00:06:06.370 --> 00:06:07.660
That must cost a fortune.

00:06:08.220 --> 00:06:10.290
As the planning director,
I have the authority

00:06:11.020 --> 00:06:13.730
to grant internal discounts
to select clients.

00:06:14.220 --> 00:06:15.780
Oh wow. You know, I've literally dreamed

00:06:15.780 --> 00:06:17.980
of going on a trip like that.

00:06:18.490 --> 00:06:20.220
I'd love to go
to the Old Town of Lijiang

00:06:20.370 --> 00:06:22.410
and stay in an inn with my loved one,

00:06:22.780 --> 00:06:24.540
and listen to the wind
in the mountains in Nepal.

00:06:25.050 --> 00:06:27.370
Just thinking about it
feels so romantic.

00:06:27.610 --> 00:06:28.580
Indeed romantic.

00:06:28.660 --> 00:06:30.460
But as a professional,

00:06:30.980 --> 00:06:32.410
I still hope you could try

00:06:32.610 --> 00:06:35.050
an in-depth tour of one place at a time.

00:06:36.140 --> 00:06:37.900
Wherever I go, I don't want to be alone.

00:06:38.140 --> 00:06:38.980
I'm scared.

00:06:39.290 --> 00:06:41.490
Our company happens to offer

00:06:41.490 --> 00:06:42.730
one-on-one personal tour guide services.

00:06:43.100 --> 00:06:43.940
So,

00:06:44.660 --> 00:06:45.900
are you the personal

00:06:46.170 --> 00:06:47.010
tour guide?

00:06:50.050 --> 00:06:50.980
Unfortunately,

00:06:52.340 --> 00:06:53.930
I probably don't have that fortune.

00:06:55.140 --> 00:06:56.100
I'm getting married.

00:06:56.660 --> 00:06:57.780
If I love someone,

00:06:58.050 --> 00:07:00.370
I wouldn't even care
whether he loves me back.

00:07:00.700 --> 00:07:01.700
Just being with him

00:07:01.810 --> 00:07:03.140
is my greatest happiness.

00:07:03.460 --> 00:07:04.370
Mr. Zhang, have you ever heard

00:07:04.370 --> 00:07:05.700
of a saying from the West?

00:07:06.170 --> 00:07:07.220
"To love for love's sake

00:07:07.900 --> 00:07:08.740
is divine.

00:07:08.980 --> 00:07:10.410
To love for being loved

00:07:11.250 --> 00:07:12.220
is a human."

00:07:13.290 --> 00:07:14.730
If I'm willing to be a divine
for you unconditionally,

00:07:14.900 --> 00:07:16.580
without asking for anything in return,

00:07:17.170 --> 00:07:19.140
can't you at least
be a human for me once?

00:07:24.020 --> 00:07:25.580
If you can't provide evidence,

00:07:26.780 --> 00:07:28.930
I absolutely refuse to believe
my boyfriend would betray me.

00:07:29.370 --> 00:07:30.660
Then, in your opinion,

00:07:31.100 --> 00:07:32.980
what counts as betrayal?

00:07:33.140 --> 00:07:33.980
Being physically intimate.

00:07:34.100 --> 00:07:36.410
Sorry, that's beyond my bottom line.

00:07:36.900 --> 00:07:37.810
Then prove it.

00:07:38.540 --> 00:07:40.020
Show me he has such intentions.

00:07:42.100 --> 00:07:42.940
Tell me,

00:07:43.700 --> 00:07:44.710
are you free tonight?

00:07:45.610 --> 00:07:46.580
Not today, sorry.

00:07:47.780 --> 00:07:49.780
I'm working part-time as a teacher.

00:07:50.540 --> 00:07:52.460
I'd quite like to see
how you are as a teacher.

00:07:54.810 --> 00:07:55.650
Sure.

00:07:56.170 --> 00:07:57.610
I'll give you a lesson another day.

00:07:58.050 --> 00:08:00.220
Alright. I'll pick you up
after work tomorrow.

00:08:01.220 --> 00:08:02.250
Don't be late, okay?

00:08:10.700 --> 00:08:12.170
Mr. Zhang, you drove past it,
didn't you?

00:08:12.610 --> 00:08:13.610
The hotel is...

00:08:13.810 --> 00:08:14.930
right around that corner.

00:08:16.490 --> 00:08:17.340
Ah,

00:08:18.140 --> 00:08:18.980
we're here.

00:08:19.980 --> 00:08:20.850
Are we here?

00:08:22.170 --> 00:08:23.610
Not quite what you expected, is it?

00:08:26.490 --> 00:08:27.850
What do you mean, not what I expected?

00:08:29.580 --> 00:08:31.170
What do you think I was expecting?

00:08:34.340 --> 00:08:35.420
You wanted to seduce me.

00:08:37.130 --> 00:08:38.980
You tried every way to get close to me.

00:08:41.700 --> 00:08:43.130
Although things like this

00:08:44.370 --> 00:08:45.530
happen in my life

00:08:45.530 --> 00:08:47.130
all the time,

00:08:47.730 --> 00:08:48.940
you're different!

00:08:50.060 --> 00:08:51.060
Why is that?

00:08:51.530 --> 00:08:52.370
I have no idea.

00:08:52.980 --> 00:08:53.820
I only know

00:08:54.420 --> 00:08:56.130
that as soon as you appear
from the elevator,

00:08:57.010 --> 00:08:58.300
your elegant demeanor

00:08:58.770 --> 00:09:00.530
radiates an alluring charm.

00:09:01.220 --> 00:09:02.980
I believe no man, however cold,

00:09:02.980 --> 00:09:04.370
could resist it.

00:09:05.370 --> 00:09:06.530
Yesterday's afternoon tea

00:09:07.130 --> 00:09:08.730
made me even more convinced of this.

00:09:08.940 --> 00:09:10.180
Right then, I told myself,

00:09:10.370 --> 00:09:12.180
"I have to be with you. I must!"

00:09:12.370 --> 00:09:13.940
But it hurts me so much, you know?

00:09:14.220 --> 00:09:15.220
Why does it hurt me?

00:09:15.530 --> 00:09:17.220
It hurts because why...?

00:09:24.850 --> 00:09:26.700
Why did she get there before you?

00:09:27.050 --> 00:09:28.940
I've already fallen for you,
shamelessly and completely.

00:09:28.950 --> 00:09:30.630
I love you. I want you right now!

00:09:31.140 --> 00:09:32.220
(Recorder)
Mr. Zhang,

00:09:33.060 --> 00:09:33.900
don't do this.

00:09:34.420 --> 00:09:35.530
There are still people outside.

00:09:35.700 --> 00:09:37.250
Who cares about them?

00:09:38.060 --> 00:09:39.820
Let go of those worldly judgments.

00:09:40.100 --> 00:09:42.530
Every extra second of waiting
feels like a crime now.

00:09:42.850 --> 00:09:44.300
Do you have anything else to say?

00:09:50.580 --> 00:09:51.700
Let's break up.

00:09:52.250 --> 00:09:53.090
Ah?

00:09:57.180 --> 00:09:59.300
(Do you know why fairy tales
in this world)

00:09:59.300 --> 00:10:02.420
(all end with the prince and princess
living happily ever after?)

00:10:05.180 --> 00:10:06.730
Snow White,

00:10:06.770 --> 00:10:08.980
try this apple.

00:10:09.300 --> 00:10:10.980
Look at this shiny red apple.

00:10:10.980 --> 00:10:12.420
It's as beautiful as you are.

00:10:12.420 --> 00:10:14.100
No, I don't want it.

00:10:14.420 --> 00:10:15.580
Come on, just try it.

00:10:15.580 --> 00:10:17.060
Such a sweet fruit!

00:10:19.850 --> 00:10:22.300
You'll never find happiness.

00:10:26.250 --> 00:10:27.180
Snow,

00:10:27.180 --> 00:10:28.850
do you want to travel the world with me?

00:10:29.010 --> 00:10:31.650
(Because what happens next
is too tragic.)

00:10:31.650 --> 00:10:33.060
(People don't want to see it.)

00:10:33.420 --> 00:10:35.010
(So, when love finally arrives,)

00:10:35.420 --> 00:10:37.530
(everyone writes an ending
as sweet as a fairy tale)

00:10:37.530 --> 00:10:40.060
(in their hearts,)

00:10:40.650 --> 00:10:43.220
(as if all the misfortunes to come)

00:10:43.580 --> 00:10:45.420
(have nothing to do with themselves.)

00:10:45.850 --> 00:10:46.730
Cinderella,

00:10:46.940 --> 00:10:48.770
did you lose this glass slipper?

00:10:51.250 --> 00:10:53.100
Two together are best.

00:10:56.730 --> 00:10:57.820
Didn't you say

00:10:58.180 --> 00:11:00.010
you'd only ever love me?

00:11:00.010 --> 00:11:01.770
Is this your love?

00:11:01.770 --> 00:11:03.370
You hypocritical big liar!

00:11:03.420 --> 00:11:05.010
Go sell your glass slippers!

00:11:05.580 --> 00:11:06.770
Liar!

00:11:06.950 --> 00:11:10.490
(But sequels are never
as good as the originals.)

00:11:35.130 --> 00:11:35.980
(Short hair.)

00:11:36.370 --> 00:11:38.060
(Blue striped suit.)

00:11:50.100 --> 00:11:50.940
Hello,

00:11:51.580 --> 00:11:52.580
a whisky, please.

00:11:59.250 --> 00:12:00.090
Thanks.

00:12:21.650 --> 00:12:22.650
Here alone?

00:12:28.220 --> 00:12:29.060
Ah.

00:12:29.300 --> 00:12:30.140
Alone.

00:12:33.300 --> 00:12:34.420
Why not have a drink?

00:12:38.130 --> 00:12:39.220
I'm not into drinking.

00:12:44.420 --> 00:12:46.300
Coming to a bar alone this late,

00:12:46.300 --> 00:12:47.460
and not drinking?

00:12:49.060 --> 00:12:50.220
You're quite interesting.

00:12:52.100 --> 00:12:53.590
Is something the matter?

00:12:53.610 --> 00:12:55.220
You're alone. I'm alone, too.

00:12:57.650 --> 00:12:58.490
Let's talk.

00:13:02.610 --> 00:13:03.980
I'm not alone.

00:13:04.610 --> 00:13:05.820
I'm waiting for a friend.

00:13:05.890 --> 00:13:07.250
Boyfriend or girlfriend?

00:13:08.010 --> 00:13:09.420
Does that matter to you?

00:13:14.940 --> 00:13:15.800
Hey,

00:13:15.820 --> 00:13:16.660
that's harsh.

00:13:16.660 --> 00:13:18.040
Hello, Gong.

00:13:18.890 --> 00:13:19.980
(Husband?)

00:13:20.650 --> 00:13:22.180
What's wrong with you?

00:13:23.220 --> 00:13:24.340
Standing me up again?

00:13:27.180 --> 00:13:28.490
I don't want to hear your useless talk.

00:13:29.220 --> 00:13:30.370
Get lost.

00:13:38.010 --> 00:13:39.250
Got stood up?

00:13:40.610 --> 00:13:41.450
Do you come here often?

00:13:45.180 --> 00:13:46.020
It's my first time.

00:13:46.180 --> 00:13:47.980
Were you stood up by your... husband?

00:13:48.650 --> 00:13:50.220
If I'm not mistaken, you...

00:13:50.220 --> 00:13:51.460
What do you want?

00:13:51.770 --> 00:13:53.460
Do you enjoy
chatting up strangers this much?

00:14:02.940 --> 00:14:04.010
What are you doing?

00:14:04.580 --> 00:14:05.770
Trying to seduce someone else's husband?

00:14:08.890 --> 00:14:09.890
What are you doing here?

00:14:11.490 --> 00:14:12.890
Can't you see I'm meeting with a client?

00:14:13.130 --> 00:14:14.010
Whatever it is, let's talk at home.

00:14:14.300 --> 00:14:15.220
Don't make a scene here.

00:14:15.530 --> 00:14:16.700
You think you're in the right?

00:14:16.980 --> 00:14:17.850
What's going on?

00:14:17.850 --> 00:14:18.940
- Betraying whom?
- Wrong person?

00:14:18.940 --> 00:14:20.370
If you can't win my heart,
don't blame me for being playful.

00:14:20.460 --> 00:14:21.300
Go home, now!

00:14:22.130 --> 00:14:22.970
You lousy scum.

00:14:23.060 --> 00:14:23.900
Where are you going?

00:14:23.980 --> 00:14:25.470
Have you caused enough trouble yet?

00:14:25.490 --> 00:14:26.530
If you're done, get home now!

00:14:27.300 --> 00:14:28.370
A total embarrassment.

00:14:28.700 --> 00:14:29.730
Did you just hit me?

00:14:30.060 --> 00:14:31.850
Today, none of you
is going to get off easy!

00:14:33.250 --> 00:14:34.490
Do you realize you've humiliated me?

00:14:34.490 --> 00:14:35.330
Huh?

00:14:35.330 --> 00:14:36.980
- Someone, help!
- Will you just behave?

00:14:37.130 --> 00:14:38.250
I said, "Behave!"

00:14:38.250 --> 00:14:39.100
You lousy scum!

00:14:42.180 --> 00:14:43.250
Excuse me, sir.

00:14:43.820 --> 00:14:45.250
Cheating is only a moral issue.

00:14:45.730 --> 00:14:47.340
Hitting someone is a legal issue.

00:14:47.700 --> 00:14:48.540
Who are you?

00:14:48.650 --> 00:14:49.730
Who I am doesn't matter.

00:14:50.610 --> 00:14:51.980
What matters is I've never met

00:14:51.980 --> 00:14:53.170
someone as shameless as you.

00:14:53.460 --> 00:14:55.100
You commit wrongdoing
and then hit people?

00:14:55.610 --> 00:14:57.100
Don't you think you've gone too far?

00:14:57.530 --> 00:14:59.100
And the rest of you,
what are you staring at?

00:14:59.300 --> 00:15:01.530
Then please, young lady, teach me.

00:15:02.220 --> 00:15:03.460
What exactly should I do?

00:15:03.700 --> 00:15:05.300
Since you're open to learning,

00:15:06.180 --> 00:15:07.130
I'll teach you then.

00:15:07.180 --> 00:15:08.020
Yeah.

00:15:09.220 --> 00:15:10.620
- You're welcome.
- She's so cool.

00:15:10.650 --> 00:15:11.580
This lesson is free.

00:15:13.130 --> 00:15:14.060
Who are you?

00:15:16.220 --> 00:15:17.530
Come on, everyone, take a look!

00:15:17.940 --> 00:15:19.490
This guy just hit a woman.

00:15:19.820 --> 00:15:21.650
Film him and post it.
Make him an internet celebrity.

00:15:22.180 --> 00:15:23.730
Let go... Let go of me!

00:15:31.700 --> 00:15:32.540
Stop crying.

00:15:33.220 --> 00:15:34.370
He's not worth it.

00:15:34.820 --> 00:15:36.090
- Okay?
- Keep walking.

00:15:36.850 --> 00:15:38.070
Don't hide, I'm talking to you.

00:15:58.700 --> 00:15:59.540
Hey,

00:16:00.730 --> 00:16:01.610
are you okay?

00:16:03.980 --> 00:16:04.820
I'm fine.

00:16:11.580 --> 00:16:12.420
Well,

00:16:12.530 --> 00:16:13.370
these shoes are for you.

00:16:13.650 --> 00:16:14.650
My friend gave them to me.

00:16:14.700 --> 00:16:15.820
Never worn, brand new.

00:16:16.580 --> 00:16:17.420
Just use them for now.

00:16:18.100 --> 00:16:19.130
Are you giving these to me?

00:16:19.940 --> 00:16:20.780
Why not?

00:16:21.580 --> 00:16:22.420
No need.

00:16:22.850 --> 00:16:24.130
I'm fine. I can manage like this.

00:16:24.340 --> 00:16:25.300
It's alright, just take them.

00:16:25.420 --> 00:16:26.260
No need to be polite.

00:16:28.700 --> 00:16:30.220
You won't get a taxi out here.

00:16:30.770 --> 00:16:31.610
I'll give you a ride.

00:16:32.700 --> 00:16:34.420
Oh, it's okay.
My ride will be here soon.

00:16:34.580 --> 00:16:36.060
Are you out this late dressed like that?

00:16:36.180 --> 00:16:37.020
It's not safe.

00:16:37.700 --> 00:16:38.540
Get in the car.

00:16:55.610 --> 00:16:56.580
You...

00:16:56.980 --> 00:16:58.460
Do you often get into cars
with strangers?

00:17:00.890 --> 00:17:03.180
Do you often let strangers
hop in your car?

00:17:04.050 --> 00:17:04.890
Yeah.

00:17:05.810 --> 00:17:07.570
I'm basically a devil in disguise.

00:17:08.140 --> 00:17:09.570
So, riding with me could be dangerous.

00:17:09.980 --> 00:17:11.090
Especially for a girl like you.

00:17:12.130 --> 00:17:12.990
Before I got in,

00:17:13.010 --> 00:17:14.770
I already sent
your license plate number to my friend.

00:17:16.220 --> 00:17:17.060
A real devil

00:17:17.140 --> 00:17:18.490
would never use a real license plate.

00:17:20.980 --> 00:17:22.490
Then... should I get out?

00:17:28.580 --> 00:17:29.430
What's wrong?

00:17:29.460 --> 00:17:31.730
I suddenly remembered
that guy in the bar.

00:17:33.140 --> 00:17:34.010
Such a coward.

00:17:34.660 --> 00:17:35.770
But what I was thinking is

00:17:36.140 --> 00:17:38.220
that I can't believe
I wore the same outfit as him.

00:17:39.900 --> 00:17:41.050
Looks like when I get back,

00:17:41.460 --> 00:17:43.460
I need to seriously review
my whole wardrobe.

00:18:05.570 --> 00:18:06.410
Here we are.

00:18:06.730 --> 00:18:07.590
Right here?

00:18:07.620 --> 00:18:08.700
- Bye.
- Bye.

00:18:24.090 --> 00:18:24.950
What's wrong?

00:18:24.980 --> 00:18:26.420
Should I invite you for coffee?

00:18:28.810 --> 00:18:30.250
It's pretty late, maybe another day.

00:18:31.490 --> 00:18:32.330
Oh.

00:18:32.880 --> 00:18:33.900
- Bye.
- Hey.

00:18:34.250 --> 00:18:35.090
Hey!

00:18:37.010 --> 00:18:39.090
Do you usually invite people over
for coffee at your place?

00:18:39.980 --> 00:18:40.820
Come on.

00:18:41.010 --> 00:18:42.860
I meant the cafe at my doorstep.

00:18:45.420 --> 00:18:46.260
Oh.

00:18:46.980 --> 00:18:47.820
Bye.

00:18:48.730 --> 00:18:49.620
Bye...

00:18:50.860 --> 00:18:51.700
Hey!

00:18:52.180 --> 00:18:53.490
What now?

00:18:54.530 --> 00:18:56.180
You said you'd treat me to coffee.

00:18:56.620 --> 00:18:57.900
How will you contact me then?

00:19:03.380 --> 00:19:04.420
Let's exchange WeChat.

00:19:06.140 --> 00:19:07.010
You scan me.

00:19:08.180 --> 00:19:09.250
I prefer others scanning me.

00:19:10.180 --> 00:19:11.050
Why?

00:19:13.420 --> 00:19:15.140
Because I'm the one
who decides whether it passes or not.

00:19:19.780 --> 00:19:20.620
(Li Xiaoxi)

00:19:24.420 --> 00:19:26.260
(Bei)

00:19:27.050 --> 00:19:28.050
Bei.

00:19:30.380 --> 00:19:31.220
Good night!

00:19:31.460 --> 00:19:32.300
Good night.

00:19:38.570 --> 00:19:39.460
Drink tea.

00:19:39.900 --> 00:19:41.140
You mean to say

00:19:41.380 --> 00:19:43.250
that men's betrayal is a law of nature?

00:19:43.770 --> 00:19:46.180
If you agree with that assumption,

00:19:46.860 --> 00:19:49.940
everything you've done
is basically a sin.

00:19:50.140 --> 00:19:52.090
I haven't destroyed any relationship.

00:19:53.050 --> 00:19:54.490
Men betray

00:19:54.900 --> 00:19:56.770
because they stop loving their partner.

00:19:57.290 --> 00:20:00.530
Whether love exists or not
isn't for you to decide.

00:20:01.530 --> 00:20:02.770
You're just helping

00:20:02.900 --> 00:20:05.250
suicidal people complete their suicide.

00:20:05.900 --> 00:20:07.530
Maybe they deserve it,

00:20:07.860 --> 00:20:09.530
but their fall shouldn't come from you.

00:20:10.330 --> 00:20:11.460
What you're doing is...

00:20:12.490 --> 00:20:14.730
shameless love murder.

00:20:15.090 --> 00:20:15.930
Ah, no.

00:20:17.180 --> 00:20:18.620
It's more like a massacre.

00:20:20.050 --> 00:20:22.220
Does it mean that if someone kills
with a kitchen knife,

00:20:22.660 --> 00:20:24.860
the knife manufacturer is guilty?

00:20:25.530 --> 00:20:26.660
If I'm guilty,

00:20:27.050 --> 00:20:29.380
what crime should those men
who betray love

00:20:29.420 --> 00:20:31.490
be charged with? Right?

00:20:32.460 --> 00:20:33.460
You asked me here today,

00:20:33.530 --> 00:20:35.180
not just to talk about this, I hope.

00:20:35.860 --> 00:20:36.700
Exactly.

00:20:37.530 --> 00:20:38.370
Here, look.

00:20:38.420 --> 00:20:39.330
Take a look.

00:20:40.460 --> 00:20:43.050
This is my daughter's boyfriend.

00:20:44.250 --> 00:20:45.620
But I know this guy

00:20:45.620 --> 00:20:47.620
doesn't really love my daughter.

00:20:48.250 --> 00:20:50.380
- Over here!
- Did you tell your daughter?

00:20:51.180 --> 00:20:52.020
I told her.

00:20:53.090 --> 00:20:54.700
That boy says she's just a client.

00:20:55.330 --> 00:20:58.050
My daughter thinks
I just don't like him.

00:20:59.980 --> 00:21:01.220
I came to see you

00:21:01.660 --> 00:21:03.380
because I want them to break up.

00:21:04.090 --> 00:21:05.410
Oh, sorry.

00:21:05.900 --> 00:21:07.620
I'm not an expert
at breaking couples up.

00:21:08.250 --> 00:21:09.090
Wait, you...

00:21:09.290 --> 00:21:10.700
Does it make any difference?

00:21:11.700 --> 00:21:13.290
What you said makes me uneasy.

00:21:13.810 --> 00:21:15.180
Then let's put it another way.

00:21:16.350 --> 00:21:17.190
Hmm.

00:21:17.220 --> 00:21:19.620
I need to find out if this man

00:21:20.050 --> 00:21:21.770
will betray my daughter.

00:21:22.530 --> 00:21:23.460
Is that alright?

00:21:25.050 --> 00:21:26.050
Oh, of course.

00:21:27.420 --> 00:21:30.220
No offense intended.

00:21:30.900 --> 00:21:31.860
I...

00:21:32.700 --> 00:21:33.730
I understand men.

00:21:34.940 --> 00:21:36.620
They are restless

00:21:37.090 --> 00:21:38.180
and impulsive.

00:21:39.810 --> 00:21:41.250
They can't handle pressure.

00:21:42.530 --> 00:21:45.420
If they meet a woman as stunning as you,

00:21:46.010 --> 00:21:47.530
I believe no matter who it is,

00:21:48.330 --> 00:21:49.490
anyone would be moved.

00:21:51.010 --> 00:21:52.050
As for me,

00:21:53.700 --> 00:21:55.530
I just hope she marries someone

00:21:57.010 --> 00:21:58.770
who can truly make her happy.

00:22:00.570 --> 00:22:02.180
So, by your logic,

00:22:03.220 --> 00:22:05.010
no matter who your daughter marries,

00:22:05.420 --> 00:22:06.810
she'll face betrayal?

00:22:07.940 --> 00:22:10.010
Perhaps all men make mistakes.

00:22:11.530 --> 00:22:13.010
But I hope her partner

00:22:13.010 --> 00:22:15.250
at least loves my daughter

00:22:15.730 --> 00:22:19.330
in his heart.

00:22:20.490 --> 00:22:22.660
Like how I love her.

00:22:23.180 --> 00:22:24.460
Cherishing her like a treasure.

00:22:25.570 --> 00:22:27.660
That would be enough.

00:22:29.010 --> 00:22:31.010
True love doesn't lead to mistakes.

00:22:31.810 --> 00:22:33.700
(I've played countless roles.)

00:22:34.180 --> 00:22:35.730
(And it seems my only line)

00:22:36.010 --> 00:22:38.810
(was to sing a lament
for their love story.)

00:22:39.380 --> 00:22:40.810
(All the men are completely defeated.)

00:22:41.460 --> 00:22:42.490
(Yet I haven't tasted)

00:22:42.490 --> 00:22:44.250
(a single hint of victory.)

00:22:44.620 --> 00:22:45.770
(The tears in the story)

00:22:45.770 --> 00:22:47.690
(constantly remind me)

00:22:48.700 --> 00:22:51.700
(that promises mean nothing
until they're fulfilled.)

00:22:52.330 --> 00:22:54.570
Feels like this show will
get pretty heartbreaking later on.

00:22:55.050 --> 00:22:56.420
Don't worry. The ending is a happy one.

00:22:56.730 --> 00:22:57.660
Have you seen it already?

00:22:58.010 --> 00:22:58.980
I looked up the spoilers.

00:22:58.980 --> 00:23:00.180
(Bei)

00:23:00.180 --> 00:23:01.700
I don't watch shows with sad endings.

00:23:02.140 --> 00:23:03.940
I've already seen
enough of that in real life.

00:23:04.330 --> 00:23:06.050
Do you think in real life,

00:23:06.860 --> 00:23:10.090
there could be men
like the male lead here?

00:23:10.700 --> 00:23:11.730
The kind who, no matter

00:23:11.810 --> 00:23:13.420
what temptation they face,
remain unmoved?

00:23:13.770 --> 00:23:14.610
Yeah.

00:23:15.050 --> 00:23:15.900
Like my Bai.

00:23:16.330 --> 00:23:17.530
Right now, there's only Yingtao

00:23:17.530 --> 00:23:18.770
in my heart.

00:23:20.050 --> 00:23:21.420
(Are you blind or what?)

00:23:23.180 --> 00:23:24.250
Wait.

00:23:25.770 --> 00:23:27.660
That doesn't sound
like something you'd ask.

00:23:28.460 --> 00:23:30.220
What did you say to me before?

00:23:30.860 --> 00:23:31.980
Men...

00:23:32.330 --> 00:23:34.700
are low creatures motivated by lust.

00:23:35.980 --> 00:23:37.530
What? Is there an exception?

00:23:38.900 --> 00:23:40.290
There is... one exception.

00:23:40.730 --> 00:23:42.380
Do you enjoy
chatting up strangers this much?

00:23:43.050 --> 00:23:44.090
Tell me more.

00:23:45.140 --> 00:23:46.140
This guy...

00:23:47.380 --> 00:23:49.220
He's not like
any of the others I've met.

00:23:49.810 --> 00:23:50.650
These shoes are for you.

00:23:50.900 --> 00:23:51.810
My friend gave them to me.

00:23:51.940 --> 00:23:53.250
Never worn, brand new.

00:23:56.770 --> 00:23:58.620
You added him with your main account?

00:23:59.380 --> 00:24:00.220
Yeah.

00:24:00.900 --> 00:24:02.140
Is he not one of your test subjects?

00:24:03.250 --> 00:24:04.090
No.

00:24:04.330 --> 00:24:05.940
But at first, I thought he was.

00:24:07.050 --> 00:24:07.900
I tested him.

00:24:08.660 --> 00:24:09.500
He passed?

00:24:12.380 --> 00:24:13.290
Sort of half and half.

00:24:14.180 --> 00:24:15.570
This shop, Zhen Guan, is his.

00:24:16.540 --> 00:24:17.460
He's the owner.

00:24:17.460 --> 00:24:18.300
(Zhen Guan)

00:24:18.570 --> 00:24:20.530
This shop does luxury authentication.

00:24:21.250 --> 00:24:23.140
I searched online
for the shop's Weibo account.

00:24:23.620 --> 00:24:24.980
From there, I found his Weibo, too.

00:24:25.620 --> 00:24:27.010
His Weibo and his Moments style

00:24:27.010 --> 00:24:27.900
are the same.

00:24:28.380 --> 00:24:29.570
He rarely posts pictures of himself.

00:24:29.980 --> 00:24:32.010
Most posts are work-related.

00:24:32.490 --> 00:24:35.010
He's usually just between home and work.

00:24:35.140 --> 00:24:36.460
On weekends, he heads out with friends.

00:24:36.570 --> 00:24:37.940
They grab dinner and play games.

00:24:38.730 --> 00:24:39.770
He's highly likely single.

00:24:40.700 --> 00:24:43.290
But social media doesn't prove much.

00:24:44.220 --> 00:24:46.380
It's all the image he wants you to see.

00:24:47.940 --> 00:24:49.330
Still, it's been three days
since he added me.

00:24:50.330 --> 00:24:51.250
But he never contacted me.

00:24:51.250 --> 00:24:52.620
(I'm Bei.)

00:24:52.620 --> 00:24:53.530
A real expert.

00:24:53.980 --> 00:24:55.090
This is definitely an expert.

00:24:55.570 --> 00:24:56.490
Think about it.

00:24:56.770 --> 00:24:58.700
Classic move. Playing hard to get.

00:25:11.940 --> 00:25:12.580
(Who can see)

00:25:13.020 --> 00:25:14.500
(Bei)

00:25:14.580 --> 00:25:16.020
(Post)

00:25:16.140 --> 00:25:19.020
(Li Xiaoxi)

00:25:27.010 --> 00:25:28.250
(Do you live alone?)

00:25:32.570 --> 00:25:34.490
Fishing to see if I'm single.

00:25:40.490 --> 00:25:41.330
(Xiaoxi)
(Yes.)

00:25:41.530 --> 00:25:42.490
(What's up?)

00:25:49.860 --> 00:25:52.490
(Bei)
(Avoid location details in photos.)

00:25:52.730 --> 00:25:54.180
(It's not safe
for a girl to live alone.)

00:25:55.290 --> 00:25:57.250
(Xiaoxi)
(You post plenty on Moments yourself.)

00:25:57.530 --> 00:25:58.660
(Bei)
(I'm male.)

00:25:59.010 --> 00:26:01.050
(My photos aren't much of a draw.)

00:26:01.770 --> 00:26:03.980
(Xiaoxi)
(What if they're just for you?)

00:26:04.900 --> 00:26:06.290
(Bei)
(What if I don't have good intentions?)

00:26:07.380 --> 00:26:08.770
(You really should be more cautious.)

00:26:12.490 --> 00:26:13.860
(Xiaoxi)
(Got it, uncle.)

00:26:14.050 --> 00:26:16.290
(Are you secretly
the anti-fraud ambassador?)

00:26:18.940 --> 00:26:20.460
(Bei)
(A friendly tip from the ambassador:)

00:26:20.530 --> 00:26:22.180
(Never send
unedited photos to strangers.)

00:26:22.420 --> 00:26:23.860
(They can reveal detailed info.)

00:26:24.050 --> 00:26:25.050
(I read a news story once.)

00:26:25.250 --> 00:26:26.770
(A woman living alone
posted photos online.)

00:26:26.770 --> 00:26:27.660
(Her address got exposed.)

00:26:27.980 --> 00:26:28.820
(Someone started targeting her.)

00:26:28.980 --> 00:26:31.380
(He snuck into her home
and hid under her bed.)

00:26:33.380 --> 00:26:35.090
(Xiaoxi)
(Don't scare me at night.)

00:26:38.050 --> 00:26:39.140
(That's pure fright.)

00:26:39.460 --> 00:26:40.490
(Will you take responsibility?)

00:26:40.620 --> 00:26:41.460
Ah!

00:26:43.700 --> 00:26:45.050
(Coming to accompany me?)

00:26:45.940 --> 00:26:47.700
(That's what you're really after?)

00:26:48.490 --> 00:26:49.620
(Bei)
(If you're still afraid,)

00:26:49.810 --> 00:26:50.650
(I...)

00:26:50.730 --> 00:26:51.980
(I can tell you a joke.)

00:26:52.140 --> 00:26:52.980
You...

00:26:53.420 --> 00:26:54.700
You're a joke yourself.

00:26:54.880 --> 00:26:55.730
(What about you?)

00:26:55.730 --> 00:26:57.900
(Do the things you say still count?)

00:26:57.900 --> 00:26:58.740
(Xiaoxi)
(What?)

00:26:59.180 --> 00:27:00.860
(Bei)
(Last time, you said you'd buy me coffee.)

00:27:00.860 --> 00:27:02.050
(You didn't forget, did you?)

00:27:04.140 --> 00:27:05.250
(Are you free tomorrow?)

00:27:07.380 --> 00:27:08.580
(Xiaoxi)

00:27:08.580 --> 00:27:09.940
(Bei)

00:27:09.940 --> 00:27:11.530
(Get some rest early. See you tomorrow.)

00:27:12.900 --> 00:27:13.740
A real expert.

00:27:14.140 --> 00:27:15.090
This is definitely an expert.

00:27:15.900 --> 00:27:17.220
Are you?

00:27:19.010 --> 00:27:21.620
(I'm curious about a man
for the first time.)

00:27:22.420 --> 00:27:24.250
(I really want to know more about him.)

00:27:24.250 --> 00:27:27.980
(Moment)

00:27:36.570 --> 00:27:37.570
I think

00:27:37.900 --> 00:27:39.220
you seem different today

00:27:39.530 --> 00:27:40.380
from last time.

00:27:41.660 --> 00:27:43.660
Compared to last time,

00:27:44.220 --> 00:27:45.180
which me do you prefer?

00:27:45.490 --> 00:27:46.810
My preference is irrelevant.

00:27:47.460 --> 00:27:48.660
Your own preference matters.

00:27:51.980 --> 00:27:54.180
The heels you left in my car last time.

00:27:55.330 --> 00:27:57.180
The heels snapped off.
They couldn't be worn anymore.

00:27:58.090 --> 00:27:58.980
They're fixed.

00:28:00.980 --> 00:28:02.460
Can you fix shoes?

00:28:02.700 --> 00:28:04.700
No, I took them to a cobbler.

00:28:05.250 --> 00:28:06.220
I just thought

00:28:06.490 --> 00:28:07.380
that worn shoes fit better

00:28:07.460 --> 00:28:09.050
than new ones, right?

00:28:09.050 --> 00:28:11.330
So I figured they should
be put to good use.

00:28:15.330 --> 00:28:16.170
Thanks.

00:28:17.730 --> 00:28:18.980
I thought you saw no difference

00:28:18.980 --> 00:28:21.380
between my heels and slippers.

00:28:22.810 --> 00:28:23.900
Slippers...

00:28:24.140 --> 00:28:25.220
are actually more practical.

00:28:26.330 --> 00:28:27.620
Oh, I didn't bring those slippers.

00:28:27.700 --> 00:28:28.860
Guess I can't return them to you now.

00:28:29.220 --> 00:28:30.140
You keep them.

00:28:30.330 --> 00:28:32.290
I should thank you
for actually using them.

00:28:32.810 --> 00:28:34.900
If unused,

00:28:35.050 --> 00:28:35.980
they'd rot in my trunk.

00:28:41.090 --> 00:28:43.290
The friend who gave you slippers
must be interesting.

00:28:44.140 --> 00:28:44.980
Yeah, pretty interesting.

00:28:48.250 --> 00:28:49.460
I haven't stepped out in ages.

00:28:49.810 --> 00:28:51.490
I've been tied up
at the shop all this time.

00:28:52.010 --> 00:28:53.140
Glad you're here with me.

00:28:53.330 --> 00:28:54.380
It's good to breathe fresh air.

00:29:05.570 --> 00:29:06.620
Interested?

00:29:08.900 --> 00:29:09.770
Very.

00:29:10.220 --> 00:29:11.090
Want to try?

00:29:14.250 --> 00:29:15.620
- Let's go.
- Sure, let's go.

00:29:19.250 --> 00:29:21.570
(1.2 meters is
the interpersonal safe distance)

00:29:21.660 --> 00:29:22.660
(between people.)

00:29:23.220 --> 00:29:25.010
(When a man wants to get closer,)

00:29:25.330 --> 00:29:27.620
(he'll find ways to bridge that space)

00:29:28.180 --> 00:29:30.090
(and spark physical contact.)

00:29:38.570 --> 00:29:40.290
Hello, have you played before?

00:29:40.900 --> 00:29:42.250
Oh, I've tried it before.

00:29:42.980 --> 00:29:44.050
Do you need instructions?

00:29:44.660 --> 00:29:46.420
Been a while,
so maybe walk us through it.

00:29:46.730 --> 00:29:47.900
Just so we don't hurt ourselves later.

00:29:48.080 --> 00:29:49.100
Alright, no problem.

00:29:50.620 --> 00:29:51.730
When you're shooting arrows,

00:29:51.750 --> 00:29:52.890
your body and the target stand

00:29:52.910 --> 00:29:55.050
should be completely side by side.

00:29:55.380 --> 00:29:58.140
Pull the bowstring to your chin
or the corner of your mouth.

00:29:58.250 --> 00:30:01.460
Line up your eyes
with the sight to aim at the target.

00:30:01.530 --> 00:30:02.860
Keep your gaze steady.

00:30:05.380 --> 00:30:06.230
Oops.

00:30:06.250 --> 00:30:07.620
Sorry, my bad.

00:30:08.730 --> 00:30:09.700
It's fine.

00:30:10.530 --> 00:30:11.570
You're actually pretty good.

00:30:12.900 --> 00:30:13.940
I used to play before.

00:30:14.250 --> 00:30:15.250
How about this?

00:30:15.660 --> 00:30:16.860
Let's have a match.

00:30:17.250 --> 00:30:19.380
The winner picks what we eat tonight.

00:30:22.050 --> 00:30:23.770
Who said I'd have dinner with you?

00:30:25.460 --> 00:30:26.460
Can't we have a meal together?

00:30:29.860 --> 00:30:30.700
Alright.

00:30:32.810 --> 00:30:33.980
Deal, then.

00:30:35.980 --> 00:30:36.820
Teacher Li,

00:30:37.770 --> 00:30:38.660
could you give me some pointers?

00:30:38.980 --> 00:30:39.900
Teacher Li?

00:30:41.810 --> 00:30:42.650
Okay.

00:30:47.940 --> 00:30:49.660
Try using this muscle.

00:30:57.330 --> 00:30:58.170
A bit lower.

00:31:00.940 --> 00:31:02.490
Picture the bullseye
as something you hate

00:31:02.570 --> 00:31:04.330
or want to escape.

00:31:05.980 --> 00:31:07.180
That way, you won't hesitate.

00:31:13.730 --> 00:31:15.420
You weren't doing that
on purpose, were you?

00:31:16.460 --> 00:31:17.330
Of course not.

00:31:17.490 --> 00:31:18.490
You're just a good teacher.

00:31:20.620 --> 00:31:21.980
What's your bullseye?

00:31:27.900 --> 00:31:28.980
And...

00:31:29.250 --> 00:31:30.090
And yours?

00:31:52.860 --> 00:31:54.140
A teacher is a teacher after all.

00:31:55.180 --> 00:31:56.620
We're equally matched.

00:31:57.420 --> 00:31:59.490
You must despise that bullseye person.

00:32:00.490 --> 00:32:01.490
You're better.

00:32:02.220 --> 00:32:03.060
Come on, let's count.

00:32:03.530 --> 00:32:04.370
Nine.

00:32:06.180 --> 00:32:07.020
Ten.

00:32:08.140 --> 00:32:08.980
Nine.

00:32:10.010 --> 00:32:10.850
Nine...

00:32:11.980 --> 00:32:12.820
Hey!

00:32:14.220 --> 00:32:15.220
Someone's here. Watch out!

00:32:15.380 --> 00:32:16.810
Are you okay? Sorry about that.

00:32:25.330 --> 00:32:26.180
Great.

00:32:26.570 --> 00:32:27.810
I lost track of the count.

00:32:28.090 --> 00:32:29.900
It's fine. You definitely won.

00:32:30.140 --> 00:32:31.010
So,

00:32:31.290 --> 00:32:33.180
you get to decide dinner tonight.

00:32:35.140 --> 00:32:36.220
I need to think about it.

00:32:38.250 --> 00:32:39.460
Take your time.

00:32:39.500 --> 00:32:40.340
No rush.

00:32:43.860 --> 00:32:45.050
- This restaurant's nice.
- Thanks.

00:32:45.050 --> 00:32:46.400
- Let's come back next time.
- Sure.

00:32:47.090 --> 00:32:48.460
Hey, let me ask you something.

00:32:48.770 --> 00:32:50.660
If your mom and I
both fell into the water,

00:32:50.730 --> 00:32:51.670
who would you save?

00:32:51.700 --> 00:32:52.540
Oh,

00:32:52.570 --> 00:32:53.490
I can't even swim.

00:32:53.660 --> 00:32:54.570
Maybe sign up for lessons first.

00:32:54.700 --> 00:32:56.620
Stop dodging the question.
Give me a real answer.

00:32:59.900 --> 00:33:02.380
If your girlfriend
asked you the same thing,

00:33:03.250 --> 00:33:04.180
what would you say?

00:33:04.900 --> 00:33:05.810
Well, that question actually

00:33:05.940 --> 00:33:07.290
has a legal answer.

00:33:08.180 --> 00:33:09.490
Saving your girlfriend is a moral duty.

00:33:09.570 --> 00:33:11.180
Saving your mother is a legal duty.

00:33:12.050 --> 00:33:15.010
If you didn't save your mom
and she died,

00:33:15.290 --> 00:33:17.220
that'd count as
intentional homicide by omission.

00:33:18.730 --> 00:33:19.980
Are you single?

00:33:21.460 --> 00:33:22.490
Why do you ask?

00:33:23.150 --> 00:33:24.010
Because with answers like that,

00:33:24.010 --> 00:33:25.570
you'll never get a girlfriend.

00:33:27.010 --> 00:33:29.180
I just don't like
hypothetical questions like that.

00:33:29.900 --> 00:33:31.810
It's like a perfectly designed trap.

00:33:32.380 --> 00:33:33.700
There's never a perfect answer.

00:33:34.250 --> 00:33:35.570
Just like the trolley problem.

00:33:35.700 --> 00:33:36.660
Choosing

00:33:37.050 --> 00:33:38.090
makes you guilty.

00:33:39.250 --> 00:33:41.010
The question is boring,

00:33:41.050 --> 00:33:43.420
but askers seek attitude.

00:33:45.140 --> 00:33:46.220
Did you hear

00:33:46.250 --> 00:33:47.730
that man's response earlier?

00:33:48.810 --> 00:33:49.650
No, I didn't.

00:33:50.010 --> 00:33:51.050
I can't swim.

00:33:51.570 --> 00:33:52.660
Let's learn together.

00:33:55.900 --> 00:33:56.740
Got it.

00:33:58.490 --> 00:34:00.860
That actually reminds me
of a friend of mine.

00:34:01.530 --> 00:34:02.980
Remember the one
I mentioned before, Gong?

00:34:05.050 --> 00:34:06.940
If it were him, he'd definitely say,

00:34:07.090 --> 00:34:09.340
"There's nothing a kiss can't fix."

00:34:13.820 --> 00:34:16.010
Why do you always call him Gong?

00:34:16.490 --> 00:34:17.380
Because his last name is Gong.

00:34:17.650 --> 00:34:18.610
As in "Gong"
from "Huanggong", the palace.

00:34:18.940 --> 00:34:20.420
All of us friends call him Gong.

00:34:21.780 --> 00:34:23.610
Such a scam nickname.

00:34:25.260 --> 00:34:26.490
Waiter, let's order.

00:34:27.090 --> 00:34:27.940
Coming.

00:34:29.900 --> 00:34:30.750
Come on.

00:34:30.750 --> 00:34:31.830
- Flowers, flowers!
- Give it to me!

00:34:34.940 --> 00:34:35.820
Close your eyes.

00:34:35.820 --> 00:34:37.780
- Close your eyes.
- Close your eyes.

00:34:38.420 --> 00:34:39.740
Here we go, three.

00:34:39.740 --> 00:34:40.780
Two.

00:34:41.380 --> 00:34:42.340
One.

00:34:46.290 --> 00:34:47.130
Marry him!

00:34:47.130 --> 00:34:48.920
Say yes!

00:34:48.920 --> 00:34:49.860
- Marry him!
- Say yes!

00:34:49.860 --> 00:34:50.940
I never understood

00:34:50.940 --> 00:34:53.260
why crowds chant "marry him".

00:34:53.270 --> 00:34:54.110
Love you forever!

00:34:54.110 --> 00:34:55.010
Truth is, most people

00:34:55.090 --> 00:34:56.130
have no idea

00:34:56.130 --> 00:34:57.010
who the proposer is

00:34:57.050 --> 00:34:59.420
or if he truly loves her.

00:34:59.860 --> 00:35:01.490
It's like enabling marriage

00:35:02.010 --> 00:35:03.340
brings universal joy.

00:35:03.860 --> 00:35:05.380
Sometimes, public proposals

00:35:06.050 --> 00:35:07.210
only move oneself,

00:35:07.650 --> 00:35:08.980
but trap others.

00:35:09.690 --> 00:35:11.210
Proposals should involve two people.

00:35:11.340 --> 00:35:13.300
Not everyone craves spotlights.

00:35:14.690 --> 00:35:15.530
You're right.

00:35:17.260 --> 00:35:18.610
One of my favorite writers

00:35:18.740 --> 00:35:20.090
once said something.

00:35:20.460 --> 00:35:21.570
The gist was,

00:35:22.610 --> 00:35:23.530
if one partner

00:35:24.010 --> 00:35:24.860
leaves early,

00:35:25.610 --> 00:35:26.530
the other

00:35:26.740 --> 00:35:28.170
grieves briefly.

00:35:28.530 --> 00:35:29.460
And soon, he or she

00:35:29.570 --> 00:35:30.530
will find new love.

00:35:31.300 --> 00:35:32.140
What we call love

00:35:32.210 --> 00:35:33.740
is sometimes just a memory,

00:35:34.260 --> 00:35:35.100
or

00:35:35.210 --> 00:35:36.210
not even a memory.

00:35:36.610 --> 00:35:38.010
Raymond Carver?

00:35:38.460 --> 00:35:39.340
You read his books, too?

00:35:39.690 --> 00:35:41.210
I really enjoy his poetry.

00:35:41.210 --> 00:35:43.130
I even imitated him back in college.

00:35:45.610 --> 00:35:46.650
So,

00:35:47.460 --> 00:35:49.820
you don't believe in eternal love?

00:35:50.690 --> 00:35:51.860
It's not that I don't believe.

00:35:52.490 --> 00:35:54.780
Sometimes, love feels

00:35:54.860 --> 00:35:55.940
too heavy for me.

00:35:56.570 --> 00:35:58.380
I don't trust easy vows.

00:35:59.460 --> 00:36:00.900
Grand promises are simple words,

00:36:01.380 --> 00:36:02.570
but they're hard to keep.

00:36:03.170 --> 00:36:04.260
Actions matter more

00:36:04.980 --> 00:36:06.130
than words, right?

00:36:12.740 --> 00:36:14.940
♪I♪

00:36:14.940 --> 00:36:16.610
Sorry, I'm probably

00:36:16.900 --> 00:36:17.900
not very romantic.

00:36:19.860 --> 00:36:20.780
You're absolutely right.

00:36:21.980 --> 00:36:22.980
Cheers to Carver.

00:36:24.570 --> 00:36:25.460
Cheers.

00:36:26.260 --> 00:36:29.780
♪I♪

00:36:29.860 --> 00:36:37.340
♪Willing to wait till time fades away♪

00:36:39.020 --> 00:36:43.460
♪Silently, I wait♪

00:36:45.100 --> 00:36:50.300
♪Waiting for you♪

00:37:04.241 --> 00:37:06.840
♪I admit it♪

00:37:06.841 --> 00:37:10.880
♪My back is against the wall♪

00:37:11.761 --> 00:37:15.280
♪There's nothing I wouldn't try to do♪

00:37:15.281 --> 00:37:19.840
♪For this feeling to have you♪

00:37:20.121 --> 00:37:22.320
♪I resist♪

00:37:22.641 --> 00:37:24.221
♪Your gaze, your lips♪

00:37:24.241 --> 00:37:26.840
♪Your touch is a gift♪

00:37:27.721 --> 00:37:31.080
♪There's no one that
I wouldn't try to fool♪

00:37:31.081 --> 00:37:34.760
♪For an image of you♪

00:37:35.761 --> 00:37:38.200
♪Take my hand again♪

00:37:38.201 --> 00:37:39.960
♪Take my mind again♪

00:37:40.041 --> 00:37:43.400
♪Break it to my heart again♪

00:37:43.801 --> 00:37:45.720
♪I'm falling down again♪

00:37:45.721 --> 00:37:47.840
♪I'm on my knees again♪

00:37:47.841 --> 00:37:51.680
♪To beg for the truth♪

00:37:53.521 --> 00:37:57.680
♪Tell me the secret of love♪

00:37:57.681 --> 00:38:02.680
♪Is that the secret of love♪

00:38:03.041 --> 00:38:06.000
♪I thought I had kept it from below♪

00:38:06.081 --> 00:38:09.480
♪Did it come from above♪

00:38:09.561 --> 00:38:13.320
♪Tell me the secret of love♪

00:38:13.561 --> 00:38:18.640
♪Is that the secret of love♪

00:38:19.041 --> 00:38:21.480
♪Gentle, passionate,
charming, terrifying♪

00:38:21.481 --> 00:38:25.920
♪What is the secret of love♪